<p><b>IV WHAT HAVE WE LEARNED ABOUT PRACTICES, PATTERNS AND BELIEFS?</b></p>

<p>A. Practices, Patterns and Beliefs</p>

<p>1. Who cares for the child?</p>

<p>2. How is the child cared for?</p>

<p>- pre-natal</p>

<p>- birth and post-partum</p>

<p>- lactation</p>

<p>- early infancy</p>

<p>- later infancy</p>

<p>B. Why Are Practices As They Are?</p>

<p>1. Lack of knowledge</p>

<p>2. Existing patterns provide norms</p>

<p>3. Beliefs</p>

<p>4. Conditions of life</p>

<p>C. Traditional and Scientific Viewpoints</p>

<p><b>V IMPLICATIONS</b></p>

<p>A. General Implications for Programming</p>

<p>B. According to Developmental Stages</p>

