<p>Nota: La informaci&oacute;n en esta tabla se tom&oacute; de los informes
finales preparados por los equipos de estudio de cada pa&iacute;s. Es evidente
que toda la informaci&oacute;n noes completo para algunos de los lugares.</p>

<p><b>III</b></p>

<p><b>METHODS AND TECHNIQUES USED IN PHASE II</b></p>

<p><b>DESCRIPTION AND ASSESSMENT</b></p>

<p>Two main approaches to the topic can be distinguished: 1) locating and
analyzing relevant written material, and 2) field work involving several
different methodologies. These correspond to the desire to tap both a scientific
literature and traditional wisdom. Methods used in each country are indicated
in Table 2.</p>

<pre>
Table 2.  Methods Used in Case Studies of Childrearing Practices
Patterns and Beliefs: Phase II
