Research Tell Us?</i>, Washington, DC: National Association for the Education
of Young Children (NAEYC).<p>
<p>
49.	Schweinhart, L. (1987), <i>When the Buck Stops Here: What It Takes to Run
Good Early Childhood Programmes</i>, Ypsilanti, Michigan: High/Scope
Educational Research Foundation.<p>
<p>
50.	Njenga, A. (1989), <i>The Preschool Education and Care Programme. A Kenyan
Experience</i>. Paper prepared for the Innocenti Global Seminar on Early Child
Development, Florence, Italy: UNICEF/International Child Development Centre.<p>
<p>
51.	Stewart, K., Alison, C. (1987), "In Search of Consistencies in Child Care
Research" in D.A. Phillips (Ed.) <i>Quality in Child Care: What Does Research
Tell Us?</i>, Washington, DC: National Association for the Education of Young
Children (NAEYC).<p>
<p>
52.	Landers, C. and Leonard, A. (1992), "Women, Work, and The Need for Child
Care," <i>Staff Working Paper No. 10</i>, New York: UNICEF/Programme
Division.<p>
<p>
53.	Torkington, K. (1989), "Training: A Process of Empowerment",
<i>Newsletter</i> (55), The Netherlands: Bernard van Leer Foundation.<p>
<p>
54.	Atkin, L. (1989), "Analysis of Instruments Used in Latin America to Measure
Psychological Development and Environmental Risk in Children From 0 to 6 Years
