TRENDS &amp; FEATURES<p>
 	CONTINUOUS ECONOMIC CRISIS: 1994 WAS MARKED <p>
	BY UNCONTROLLED INFLATION &amp; HIGH DEVALUATION<p>
 	UNEMPLOYMENT FLUCTUATES WITHIN<p>
	A NARROW RANGE AT THE COST OF FURTHER<p>
	SUBSIDIES TO THE GOVERNMENT SECTOR<p>
 	THE MANUFACTURING SECTOR HAS BOTTOMED OUT <p>
	IN 1994 BY 0.2 %<p>
 	ANALYSTS ARE UNANIMOUS THAT POLITICAL STABILITY <p>
	AND PRIVATIZATION ARE THE KEY TO POSITIVE <p>
	DEVELOPMENT IN BULGARIA NOW<p>
	The above figures and short comments provide in a nutshell the overall
economic environment for our research.<p>
