   and                                                                                  
Maternity                                                                               
Allowance  <br> 
<pre>
                                                                            
             1980       1985       1989       1990       1991       1992       1993     
Bulgaria                            2.6        2.7        3.3        2.5        1.7     
 Hungary      2.5        2.7        4.0        4.0        4.6        4.7                
 Poland                             2.1        1.7        2.3        2.2                
 Romania                            3.2        3.1        1.9        1.1                

</pre>
Source:
 ICDC, 1994, pg. 97<p>
<p>
And the percentage of family income that is provided through family allowances
is decreasing, with the exception of Poland.  (See Table 14)<p>
<p>
<p>


  Table                                                           
   14:                                                            
  Child                                                           
Allowance                                                         
/Average                                                          
  Wage                                                            
  Ratio                                                           
   (%)                                                            
 2-child                                                          
 Family   <br>
<pre>
                                                        
             1989       1990       1991       1992       1993     
Bulgaria     12.8        9.8       13.8       10.7        9.0     
 Hungary     20.5       21.8       19.9       18.1       17.0     
