  of the                                                                      
  parent                                                                      

</pre>

      Source: T&aacute;j&eacute;koztat&oacute; a csal&aacute;d-,gyermek-,
&eacute;s ifj&uacute;s&aacute;gv&eacute;delemr&otilde;l (Report on Family Care,
    <p>
       Child-, and Youth Care). N&eacute;pj&oacute;l&eacute;ti
Miniszt&eacute;rium 1989, 1990, 1991, 1993.<p>
<p>
The drastic increase in the number of children at risk, with a simultaneous
decrease in the number of protective-caring measures indicate that Social
Services Departments for Children Under Age are less and less able to exercise
control over the problems involved, that is, they do not possess an adequate
set of means for overcoming conditions of risk.<p>
<p>
<b>Educational Allowance</b><p>
<b></b>

<pre>
                      1989             1990             1991             1992        
Number of            153,600          215,353          526,824          651,324      
families                                                                             
supported                                                                            
Number of            348,617          375,243         1,023,162        1,179,119     
children under                                                                       
age supported                                                                        
