<p>
The drastic increase of state help both in terms of the number of cases and the
sums paid has been warranted by the soaring number of those at risk, due to
financial reasons, in recent years. More than four times as many families, and
children under age were given educational allowance in 1992 than in  1989. The
number of families and children under age entitled for educational allowance or
educational support grew threefold in three years. The increased funds for
support (approx. 630 million HF-s in 1989, and 3.3 billion HF-s in 1992)  were
provided from the central budget through increasing the support bracket of
local authorities on the basis of competition, where applicants had to indicate
the figures of the expenses planned originally for support of the local
authorities, and also the main social indices of their settlements.<p>
<u>Special services in child and youth protection</u><p>
<u></u>When the means of protective child care do not prove to be sufficient in
eliminating  the risk condition of the child under age, the child is removed
from his or her family. The number and relative proportion of children under
age placed into state care has steadily decreased within the population of
children under age.<p>
<p>
