	 72 hours supplementary course for directors of day care centers<p>
<b></b><p>
<b></b>The number and ratio of staff working in day care centers is similar to
those in the previous years.  There were 13 514 people all together on December
31, 1994.:<p>
	54% of them were caregivers<p>
	10.6% of them were pediatricians, psychologists, pedagogues, special
educators, and 		catering and administrative staff<p>
	35.5% of them were manual workers (cleaning, laundry, gardening, etc.).<p>
